2. I wanted to unmanage the resource from a Terraform, going forward, I don't want to manage any resources from the account is via the Terraform. So how do you unmanage it?

Step 1 — Remove from state file:

# Remove specific resource
terraform state rm aws_instance.myserver

# Remove all resources
terraform state rm $(terraform state list)

Step 2 — Remove from main.tf:

# Delete or comment out the resource block
# from your main.tf

# Before:
resource "aws_instance" "myserver" {
    ami           = "ami-12345"
    instance_type = "t2.micro"
}

# After:
# delete this block completely

Why both steps needed:

Remove from state only:
→ next terraform plan tries to CREATE again ❌

Remove from main.tf only:
→ next terraform plan tries to DESTROY it ❌

Remove BOTH:
→ Terraform completely forgets resource ✅
→ Resource still running in AWS ✅
→ No create, no destroy ✅

If you want to unmanage EVERYTHING:

# Option 1 - delete state file
rm terraform.tfstate

# Option 2 - remove all from state
terraform state rm $(terraform state list)

# Then delete or archive all .tf files
