what happens if a provider is getting upgraded? for example, you are in an AWS 7.5 provider, and that needs to be updated to 7.6. It's a major version. So how do you plan for this?

Step 1 — Check current version:

# versions.tf
terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 7.5"    ← current
    }
  }
}

Step 2 — Read changelog first:

Always check before upgrading:
https://github.com/hashicorp/terraform-provider-aws/releases

Look for:
├── Breaking changes    ← most important
├── Deprecated fields   ← need to update code
├── New required args   ← need to add to main.tf
└── Removed resources   ← need to replace

Step 3 — Test in dev first:

NEVER upgrade prod directly

Order:
dev workspace first    → test upgrade
qa workspace second    → verify
prod workspace last    → after confirmed safe

Step 4 — Update version in code:

# versions.tf
terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 7.6"    ← updated
    }
  }
}

Step 5 — Run upgrade commands:

# Update provider
terraform init -upgrade

# Check what will change
terraform plan

# Look for:
# ├── any resource changes
# ├── any deprecation warnings
# └── any errors

Step 6 — Fix breaking changes:

# Example: field name changed in 7.6
# Before 7.5:
resource "aws_instance" "server" {
  security_groups = ["sg-12345"]    ← old field
}

# After 7.6:
resource "aws_instance" "server" {
  vpc_security_group_ids = ["sg-12345"]   ← new field
}

Step 7 — Apply in order:

# Dev first
terraform workspace select dev
terraform apply
# verify everything works ✅

# QA next
terraform workspace select qa
terraform apply
# verify everything works ✅

# Prod last
terraform workspace select prod
terraform apply
# verify everything works ✅

